━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
💡 Use Case Recommendations

📋 In-Memory Storage - Use When:
   ✅ Testing and development
   ✅ Short-lived sessions
   ✅ Maximum performance needed
   ✅ Data can be regenerated
   ❌ DON'T use for production data

💾 Sled Storage - Use When:
   ✅ Production deployments
   ✅ Data must persist
   ✅ ACID transactions needed
   ✅ Multiple instances (file-based isolation)
   ✅ Good balance of speed & durability

🚀 Future Backends:
   • PostgreSQL (multi-user, enterprise)
   • SQLite (single-file, portable)
   • RocksDB (high-throughput)
   • S3-compatible (cloud-native)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
🎯 Backend Selection Guide

Development:
   → In-Memory (fastest iteration)

Testing:
   → In-Memory (isolated, fast)

Production (Single Instance):
   → Sled (embedded, no ops overhead)

Production (Multi-Instance):
   → PostgreSQL (future) or Sled with file-per-instance

High Throughput:
   → In-Memory with periodic Sled snapshots


